# rhcs_wif_config (Resource)

Registers a Workload Identity Federation (WIF) configuration in OCM for an
OSD cluster on Google Cloud Platform. The resource returns a blueprint
(workload_identity_pool, service_accounts, support, custom roles) that the
GCP side then provisions via the `hashicorp/google` provider; see
`examples/create_osd_gcp_cluster_full/modules/wif-gcp/` for a reference
implementation.

Best practice: use **one WIF config per cluster**. WIF configs are
version-specific (`openshift_version`); one-per-cluster simplifies the
lifecycle (create/destroy together) and avoids upgrade conflicts when
clusters differ in version.

